ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Let me check a few more critical items:\n1. Check if there are migrat
ion files for match_actions, matches, conversations, conversation_participants, 
blocks tables\n2. Check the database entities index to see if all entities are e
xported\n3. Check the `blocks` entity was moved and if blocks.module is updated 
correctly\n4. Check if there\'s a `matching-events.yaml` contract\n5. Check the 
mobile tests for match_list_cubit\n6. Check the design system golden tests\n\nI\
've already found some important issues:\n- No migrations for matching-related t
ables! The entities exist but no migrations. Per db.md: "新增 Entity 必须同时提
交 Migration"\n- No `matching-events.yaml` file. Per api.md: "契约文档：`docs/ap
i-contracts/<module>-events.yaml`（事件名、Payload Schema、触发时机）"\n- The `M
atchingGateway.handleConnection` doesn\'t validate profile completion - it only 
validates JWT. But per PRD, incomplete profiles shouldn\'t be able to use matchi
ng. However, since it\'s just a socket connection, and the REST APIs are guarded
, this might be acceptable. But the socket could still receive events. Let me th
ink... The PRD says "后端所有匹配相关 API 统一增加 ProfileCompletionGuard" - the
gateway is not an API, it\'s a websocket. But should incomplete users receive ma
tch notifications? Probably not, since they can\'t match. This is a potential is
sue.\n- In `MatchingService.recordSwipeAction`, when a duplicate key exception h
appens, it catches and continues. But for a `pass` action, it also clears the ca
che. For a duplicate `pass`, this means the cache is cleared again. That\'s fine
.\n- In `MatchingService.getRecommendations`, when cache miss and lock acquisiti
on fails, it waits 500ms and retries. If still no cache, it returns empty. This 
could be a UX issue but not blocking.\n- The `buildRecommendations` method doesn
\'t filter out blocked users when reading from cache. Wait, the cache only store
s user_ids and scores. When building from cache, it just fetches profiles by IDs
. But what if someone was blocked or already matched after the cache was built? 
The cache is cleared on swipe and match, but there\'s a race condition. However,
this is a minor issue.\n\nWait, looking more carefully at `queryCandidatesFromDb
`:\n- The SQL excludes `match_actions` where `actor_id = ?` (current user acted)
\n- AND `actor_id FROM match_actions WHERE target_id = ? AND action = \'pass\'` 
(people who passed on current user)\n- AND `matches` in either direction\n- AND 
`blocks` in either direction\n\nBut in `buildRecommendations` (cache hit path), 
it does NOT re-apply these exclusions. If the cache was built before a block/mat
ch/action, stale data could be served. But the cache is cleared on swipe actions
. However, blocks are not handled - if someone blocks a user, the cache isn\'t c
leared. This is a potential issue but might be out of scope.\n\nLet me check the
blocks module to see if it clears cache.',
    encrypted=None
)
